19","number":52519,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Define `CompoundPeriod` conversion/constructor for `Real`","user":{"login":"charleskawczynski","id":1880641,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4ODA2NDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1880641?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski","html_url":"https://github.com/charleskawczynski","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/charleskawczynski/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"This PR defines conversions, or rather, `CompoundPeriod` constructors that accept `Real` numbers. For example (from the tests added):

